IV. Settings

  DOS:
  - Set LANG environmental variable to set language (e.g. LANG=en).
  - Edit CONFIG/TUBES2*.CFG file to set program.
  - For update from internet function, install packet driver for your NIC
    (e.g. C:\DRIVERS\3C509\PKTDVR\3C5X9PD 0X60).
  - Edit CONFIG/WATTCP.CFG file (network settings).
  - If a WATTCP.CFG environmental variable exists and its value is good,
    you can skip previous step.

  FreeBSD, Linux:
  - Set LANG environmental variable to set language (e.g. LANG=en).
  - Use 'File/Settings' in main menu to set application.

  Windows:
  - Use 'File/Settings' in main menu to set application.

